oyer owes more to the villain of legend than to the bishop or the writer. For the most part this name is of Irish origin; however, it was in use in Yorkshire, especially among the Askes and the Bartons, from the 12th to the 16th centuries. In this case, the name was derived from Conan, Earl of Richmond, and is of Breton origin."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Conan de Brittany I was born in 1430, in Rennes, Ille-et-Vilaine, Brittany, France. He had at least 1 son with Ermengarde D'anjou. He died on 9 September 1488, at the age of 58."},"et":{"1430–9 September 1488":"1430–9. september 1488","1431–1508":"1431–1508","1450–1508":"1450–1508","1430–1488":"1430–1488","1488":"1488","1431":"1431","1430":"1430","1450":"1450","9 September 1488":"9. september 1488","1508":"1508","Rennes, Rennes, Ille-et-Vilaine, Bretagne, France":"Rennes, Ille-et-Vilaine, Bretagne, Prantsusmaa"},"fi":{"1430–9 September 1488":"1430–9. syyskuuta 1488","1431–1508":"1431–1508","1450–1508":"1450–1508","1430–1488":"1430–1488","1488":"1488","1431":"1431","1430":"1430","1450":"1450","9 September 1488":"9. syyskuuta 1488","1508":"1508","Rennes, Rennes, Ille-et-Vilaine, Bretagne, France":"Rennes, Ille-et-Vilaine, Bretagne, Ranska"},"fr":{"1430–9 September 1488":"1430–9 septembre 1488","1431–1508":"1431–1508","1450–1508":"1450–1508","1430–1488":"1430–1488","1488":"1488","1431":"1431","1430":"1430","1450":"1450","9 September 1488":"9 septembre 1488","1508":"1508","Rennes, Rennes, Ille-et-Vilaine, Bretagne, France":"Rennes, Ille-et-Vilaine, Bretagne, France","lifeSummary":"Conan de Brittany I est né en 1430, à Rennes, Ille-et-Vilaine, Bretagne, France. Il a eu au moins 1 fils avec Ermengarde D'anjou. Il est décédé le 9 septembre 1488, à l’âge de 58 ans."},"de":{"1430–9 September 1488":"1430–9. September 1488","1431–1508":"1431–1508","1450–1508":"1450–1508","1430–1488":"1430–1488","1488":"1488","1431":"1431","1430":"1430","1450":"1450","9 September 1488":"9. September 1488","1508":"1508","Rennes, Rennes, Il